Text.Value: You think you're free? Then let's tighten your chain.

EditorData.stateContext: Astarion no longer in pain, skeleton no longer concentrating on spell

Text.Value: But the master says no. Says he needs all of your blood on the inside for the Mass.
You have become your own master. Deny him.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Chris] [Skel] OUT skeleton breaks concentration and stumble backwards in shock.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The runes on Astarion's back stop glowing, as their power fades. The skeleton's concentration is broken. It staggers backwards, and looks at you with shock - it's jaw hanging open
EditorData.SFXTags: [KC] The rune starts to fizz out and then stops glowing. Astarion brakes frees out of his magical bounds and when that happens a wave blast was sent out in the air
EditorData.VFXTags: [KC] The rune starts to fizz out and then stops glowing. Astarion brakes frees out of his magical bounds and when that happens a wave blast was sent out in the air

Text.Value: Focus your mind to construct a mental fortress, and shelter within it.
He has no power over me anymore.
*But you're not alone in this fight. Your tadpole is aggressively territorial - and you are its territory.*
*Cazador's presence rises in your mind, a towering red wave that seems capable of drowning the world.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Chris] [AST] Mindmeld like psychic struggle. Potentially REUSE

EditorData.stateContext: Skeleton concentrating on maintaining power of rune - rune on Astarion's back glowing. astarion in pain

Text.Value: I'll never do what he tells me again - I'd rather die.
Oh, you'll do both. You'll do whatever he requires.
*And it shatters your will entirely, smashing your defences and leaving you broken and gasping for air. You cannot deny him.*
*Cazador's presence rises in your mind, a towering red wave that seems capable of drowning the world.*
Impossible. You're a spawn - know your place!
Nasty little runaway. But you always find your way back to Godey, hmm?
I'll do whatever Cazador wants - just let me go.
*And then it is inside you, clogging your nostrils and throat with a sickening sweetness. You cannot fight back. You cannot reject it.*
And he wants you to die. But not yet.
*It's no good. You are in his domain, and he will not be denied. His presence fills your mind, erasing your personality.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Chris] [AST] Mindmeld like psychic struggle. Potentially REUSE

Text.Value: Yes, good. All he wants is your obedience.
But he needs you obedient too. No barking, no biting, no struggling - a well-behaved little doggie.
*And as it threatens to consume you completely, you swallow it down, and reject it as if it were an unpleasant clot in a fine vintage.*
Feign obedience and acceptance while you seek a means to fight back.
*Cazador - your master, your lord, your creator. His will tightens around you once again, and it is as if you never escaped him.*
*But it crashes against the wall of sheer willpower you have erected, and breaks. He has no hold on you.*
*Cazador's presence fills your mind, like blood in a blister. Once inside, it seeks a vulnerability to exploit, a weakness to latch onto.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Chris] [AST] Mindmeld like psychic struggle. Potentially REUSE

Text.Value: *A familiar stink fills your nostrils - you're back in 'the Kennel', where you spent days, tendays being tortured by Cazador's sadistic servant Godey.*
*Like blood in a blister, Cazador's presence fills your mind. You accept it, bow to it, allow it to wash over you in a red tide.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Chris] [AST] Mindmeld like psychic struggle. Potentially REUSE

Text.Value: *And it finds nothing. You expel him from your mind as if he were an unpleasant clot in a fine vintage.*
*All that you've seen since the crash - all the wonders and horrors - suddenly seem inconsequential. Only one thing matters.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Chris] [Skel] Activates the Runes using magic gestures TBD. IN and LOOP.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The skeleton clenches its fist, and the runes on Astarion's back begin to glow. It causes him pain, and he reacts.
EditorData.SFXTags: [KC] Godey cast a spell to bind Astarion. Rune on Astarion's back begins to glow, causing Astarion pain
EditorData.VFXTags: [KC] Godey cast a spell to bind Astarion. Rune on Astarion's back begins to glow

Text.Value: If I had my way, I'd saw off your legs - that'd put a stop to your wandering.
*It sends out a wall of telepathic force, shattering Cazador's will. His hold on you is broken once more.*

Synopsis:
Dialog in which a Godey performs a ritual on Astarion.
The goal of the ritual to make Astarion obedient to make sure he doesn't interfere with the ritual.
